Sarkozy Says NATO Strikes Must Continue Until Qaddafi Is No Longer Threat

-- B y   J a m e s   H e r t l i n g
-- 
2011-09-01T18:59:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/sarkozy-says-nato-strikes-must-continue-until-qaddafi-is-no-longer-threat.html
French President  Nicolas Sarkozy 
said that NATO strikes must continue in  Libya  until Muammar
Qaddafi is no longer a threat. Sarkozy made his comments today
to reporters after a Libya conference in Paris.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Hertling in Paris at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
